name: Hypertension, Progress, Chief Complaint Non Coded
Hypertension, Diagnostic Criteria
description:
- Normal blood pressure: systolic less than 120 mmHg and diastolic less than 80 mmHg
- Prehypertension: systolic 120 to 139 mmHg or diastolic 80 to 89 mmHg
- Hypertension:
- Stage 1: systolic 140 to 159 mmHg or diastolic 90 to 99 mmHg
- Stage 2: systolic greater than equal to 160 or diastolic greater than equal to 100 mmHg
- Stage 3: greater than 180 systolic and greater than 110 diastolic

description: Poorly understood mechanism, but risk factors above
